steps.instruction:
1. Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium
2. Add curry paste and cook, stirring frequently, until paste begins to stick to bottom of saucepan and is very fragrant, 23 minutes
3. Whisk in coconut milk and bring to a simmer
4. occasionally, until mixture turns darker in color and is slightly reduced, about 3 minutes
5. Remove saucepan from heat and whisk in peanut butter, vinegar, fish sauce, and honey
6. Season to taste with salt; it should be well seasoned since the things you are dipping in it may not be (i.e., boiled eggs, cukes, etc.)
7. Let cool to room temperature, then transfer to an airtight portable container and chill
